sql:
SELECT post_id, post_content, post_engagement
FROM posts
WHERE post_engagement < (SELECT AVG(post_engagement) FROM posts);

external_knowledge:
Last year refers to the year 2022 in this context;
Simulated comments are artificial comments generated for testing or demonstration purposes;
Average simulated comment count greater than 100 indicates posts that, on average, were expected to have a high level of engagement based on simulated data;
The Unix timestamp is a measure of time in seconds since January 1, 1970, for the post time.

- "Whispers" metaphorically refer to comment texts;
- "Receptive ears" metaphorically refer to high engagement scores indicating that comments have been well-received or have garnered significant attention;
- "Echo chamber" symbolizes the platform where posts and comments are shared;
- "Voices" metaphorically represent the text content of the comments;
- "Resonance stirred" refers to the engagement score of the posts;
- "Most reverberated sounds" indicate the posts with the highest engagement scores.

